author: pochs@sunherald.com Twitter: PatrickOchs (PATRICK OCHS)
title: SEC Power Rankings: Tigers take top spot; Dawgs take a tumble
text:
Order a reprint of this story 
Florida running back Kelvin Taylor celebrates by jumping on quarterback Will Grier (7) after their 38-10 win over Mississippi in an NCAA college football game Saturday, Oct. 3, 2015, in Gainesville, Fla. (AP Photo/Phelan M. Ebenhack) PHELAN M. EBENHACK â€” AP 
1. LSU (3): Tigers continue to just win. As long as Leonard Fournette is healthy, LSU will be in every game. 
2. Texas A&M (4): Aggies offense continues to click. 
3. Alabama (5): Who said the Nick Saban Era at Bama is over? 
4. Florida (7): How 'bout the flu-ridden Gators? Would have loved to see what a healthy squad could accomplish. 
5. Ole Miss (1): Rebels couldn't have played much worse Saturday. Their weak OL was really exposed. 
6. Mississippi State (6): There won't be many teams that can limit the Aggies to 30 points. 
7. Georgia (2): On the bright side, Nick Chubb's 13th straight 100-yard game bested Herschel Walker's record. 
8. Kentucky (8): It took OT, but UK topped that scrappy bunch from Eastern Kentucky. 
9. Missouri (10): No Maty Mauk needed as Tigers devour USC. Saban is alive and well at Bama; but what about Spurrier? 
10. Arkansas (12): Maybe this win rights the ship for the Hogs. 
11. Tennessee (9): Another week, another lead lost. 
12. Auburn (11): Auburn really showed San Jose State who belongs in the SEC right now. 
13. South Carolina (13): Remember when Spurrier held that press conference to say he wasn't going anywhere? 
14. Vanderbilt (14): Best performance of the season yields Vandy a win over a nice MTSU team.
